                <head>Local Board of Health of Balsall Heath</head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Balsall Heath</placeName>, <date
                        ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1865-05-03">May 3, 1865</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">Resolution passed at a meeting held by the Local Board of
                        Health of Balsall Heath</hi>.</p>
                <p>At a meeting of the Local Board of Health for the district of Balsall Heath, near
                    Birmingham, in the county of Warwick, held at their offices in Vincent street,
                    Balsall Heath, aforesaid, on Wednesday, the 3d day of May, 1865, it was</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Unanimously resolved</hi>, That this board desires to express
                    its deepest sympathy with the government of the United States of America, and
                    Mrs. Lincoln, in the bereavement which both have sustained by the lamented death
                    of the late President, and to record its horror and detestation of the crime
                    which has caused so great a national loss.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>SAMUEL BRIGGS,</signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chairman</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
